<TITLE> Indian diplomat to be new head of Commonwealth </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kampala, Nov 24 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The 53-nation Commonwealth of mainly former British colonies on Saturday appointed an Indian diplomat, Kamalesh Sharma, as its next secretary-general. Sharma, the Indian High Commissioner in London, will take over on April 1 from New Zealand's Don McKinnon, who has done the job for two terms, or eight years. "It is a tough job I have taken over but I do so with confidence and enthusiasm ... the Commonwealth is a great global good," Sharma said when his appointment was announced by McKinnon during a summit of the group in Uganda. The Commonwealth's members represent 1.8 billion people, or more than a quarter of the world's population. Sharma beat Maltese Foreign Minister Michael Frendo to the job
